{"id": 243240154, "title": "WestJet mechanics walk off job despite feds imposing arbitration", "text": "WestJet says their mechanics are walking off the job on Friday night despite the federal government announcing the dispute was heading to binding arbitration. The airline says the Aircraft Mechanics Fraternal Association (AMFA) have notified of a plan to commence a strike action as of 7:30 p.m. In a statement, WestJet says they are outraged the union is going ahead with the job action despite orders from the federal labour minister. \u201cThe government has officially stepped in to provide binding arbitration and ensure we get to a resolution,\u201d reads the statement from Diederik Pen, President of WestJet Airlines and Group Chief Operating Officer. \u201cThe only reason for this union to continue with a strike action is to create damage, disrupt the travel plans of thousands of Canadians over the July long weekend and to inflict significant costs on our business.\u201d More to come.", "summary": "WestJet says their mechanics are walking off the job on Friday night despite the federal government announcing the dispute was heading to binding arbitration. The airline says the Aircraft Mechanics Fraternal Association (AMFA)\u00a0have notified of a plan to commence a strike action as of 7:30 p.m. In a statement, WestJet says they are outraged the [&#8230;]", "url": "https://toronto.citynews.ca/2024/06/28/westjet-mechanics-strike-canada-day-long-weekend/", "image": "https://toronto.citynews.ca/wp-content/blogs.dir/sites/10/2024/06/c5bc0278-2d56-4be0-be2e-ec16fd53f62c.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 01:22:22", "author": "Michael Ranger", "authors": ["Michael Ranger"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": -0.575}